feed.title: Otways Bioscan – Lepidoptera
feed.subtitle:
This lepidoptera survey is conducted by Museums Victoria and Parks Victoria in conjunction with Moths of Victoria team members. **Observations added to this group are restricted to those made during the survey events.
Components of the Bioscan project: • Make comparisons between recently burnt areas with unburnt areas • Prepare a booklet
NOTE: Your information is valuable to the creation of a comprehensive list of species occurring in the Otways. Please join the NatureShare group 'Otway Ranges – Moths'

entry.title: Calamidia hirta
entry.content: Plain brown, narrow-winged moth with wingspan approaching 40 mm. Plain yellow hindwings.

entry.title: Gallaba eugraphes
entry.content: Medium sized, distinctive moth. The female is similar but bipectinate antennae are not as broad as with the males.

entry.title: Tineodes adactylalis
entry.content: Small moth; Narrow forewings folded longitudinally giving a distorted appearance.

entry.title: Atheropla decaspila
entry.content: Small, cream coloured moth with dark rounded spots along the termen; dark speckled transverse baron outer fifth; five small but obvious spots on forewing. Upturned palpi curved back over head.

entry.title: Heteroteucha parvula
entry.content: Adult moth; Forewing yellow on inner two thirds with outer third suffused with orange; dark transverse line at two thirds extending from trailing edge to middle.
